args: All right, let's give this a try.\nI need to point the mana\nI've gathered outward...
That's right. Just relax and focus\nthe mind on who you are healing.
I really did it! Oh, I'm so happy!
That's another step closer to being a\nfull-fledged nurse. ...Er, right?
Indeed. Now you just need to increase\nyour success rate and make yourself\never more dependable.
Thank you for teaching me, Cleo.
Is it true you can use healing magic\nnow, Aeleen? That's great!
I owe it all to Cleo for being\nsuch a good teacher.
Hold on a moment... Are you hurt,\nPrince {player_name}?
Yes, of course. ...Well, if you ever ARE,\nknow that I'll be more than happy to set\nyour ailments to rights.
I'm going to study hard and become\nthe finest nurse in the land!
Gaaah... Owwww... I tell ya, Sarisse's\nbody blows get more deadly by the day.
What, this? Nah, this is just more of a...\nWell, somethin' I'm used to, I guess.
Oh. Well, that's good. Er, but if you\never ARE injured, come to me!
You got it. And thanks for the concern!\n...Er, that WAS concern, right?
I can't believe it's taken me this long\nto notice you were fraying.
But don't worry, Matilda; as soon as I'm\ndone sewing you back up, I'll give you\nall the snuggles in the wor—OW!
You pricked yourself with a sewing needle!\nYou need painkillers! Iodine! Bandages!
It was just a simple pinprick.\nI'm not even bleeding.
Aeleen, how long have you been\nstanding outside my door?

Oh, from right around the time you said,
＂But don't worry, Matilda; as soon as
I'm done sewing you back up, I'll give
you all the snuggles in the wor—OW!＂
Uuurgh... Just ate too much for dinner...\nWell, technically it was second dinner...\nPlus an early breakfast... And snacks...
Well, that's not helpful at all!
Er, SHOULD it be helpful?\n...Wait, where ya goin'?!
Okay, so I was taking a nap earlier and\nsorta fell off the desk. ...Don't laugh.
Anyway, Aeleen comes running to see if\nI'm hurt, but when I tell her that I'm fine,\nshe gets all huffy and leaves!
Heh. I suppose it's normal to want\nto make use of a new skill.
Anyway, do you want me to read you the\nrest of that faerie tale we started earlier?
Do I ever! Crack that sucker open\nlike an egg in a hammer store!
I'm going to take that as a yes.\nNow where were we...?
Oh man, paper cuts are the wors—
Oh, I'm sorry! I didn't mean to scare you!\nI just heard someone cry out in pain\nand rushed in to see if I could help.
Er, I just cut my finger on the edge\nof one of the pages here.
You sound weirdly happy about that.
What? Of course not! I would never be\nhappy to see someone hurt!
But now that I've finally met someone\nwho's really injured, I'm so... *sniff*
Give me your hand and let me heal you,\nPrince {player_name}.
(Heh. I don't think she's aware of how\nshe's coming across to everyone.)
Right. First, I need to focus on the mana\naround me and harmonize with it...
Then I need to point the mana\nI've gathered outwards...
